OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,497,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F469A1773511563
OL,3,CPay-out given to Sainsbury's worker
OL,4,Cleft out of social media post
OL,6,FAccompanying the post was a photo of
OL,7,Fevery regional store manager named and
OL,8,Ftagged, except Mr Cooper, the tribunal
OL,9,Fheard.
OL,11,FHe suffered "untold further damage" to
OL,12,Fhis health along with the "angst" of
OL,13,Fhaving to field questions from friends
OL,14,Fand colleagues asking him if he had
OL,15,Fleft Sainsbury's, the tribunal heard.
OL,17,FMr Hourihan said that as Mr Cooper had
OL,18,Fdeleted WhatsApp and said he did not
OL,19,Fwish to be contacted, he thought it
OL,20,Fbest to leave him off the post.
OL,26,@sD@MOUsD@cO]tD@[OUtD@aO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,497,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F469A1773511563
OL,3,CPay-out given to Sainsbury's worker
OL,4,Cleft out of social media post
OL,6,FHe added that he did not have a photo
OL,7,Fof Mr Cooper and thought it
OL,8,Finappropriate to ask.
OL,10,FAfter many discussions over when Mr
OL,11,FCooper would return to work he was
OL,12,Fdismissed in June 2023.
OL,14,FHe sued for disability discrimination,
OL,15,Fharassment, unfavourable treatment and
OL,16,Funfair dismissal.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,497,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F469A1773511563
OL,3,CPay-out given to Sainsbury's worker
OL,4,Cleft out of social media post
OL,6,FThe panel ruled: "The cause of the
OL,7,Ftreatment was the conscious thought
OL,8,Fprocess of Matt Hourihan to not
OL,9,Finclude (Mr Cooper) from the post as
OL,10,Fhe was absent and therefore this
OL,11,Famounted to unfavourable treatment
OL,12,Fbecause of something arising from
OL,13,Fdisability."
OL,15,FMr Cooper's claims of disability
OL,16,Fdiscrimination and unfair dismissal
OL,17,Fwere dismissed by the tribunal.
OL,26,@nD@ROUuD@LO]
